  "title": "Cybersecurity Engineer",
  "description": "<ul><li><strong>Strong hands-on SailPoint implementation (IdentityIQ and/or IdentityNow) - End-to-end SailPoint implementation including application onboarding, connectors, Joiner-Mover-Leaver (JML) workflows, access certification campaigns, role modeling/mining, SoD policies, integrations with HR/AD, UAT and production rollout</strong></li><li><strong>IAM & IGA engineering (beyond operations/support): Hands-on design and implementation of IAM governance processes, identity lifecycle management, RBAC/ABAC, access reviews, audit & compliance alignment</strong></li><li>Hands-on deployment & management of native cloud security solutions (AWS, Azure, OCI, GCP) - Cloud IAM/security services integration with SailPoint preferred</li><li>Hands-on with at least 2 tools: XDR (Trend Micro Vision One), Vulnerability Mgmt (Tenable SC / Tenable.io), DLP (Trellix)- Engineering, rollout, tuning, and operational optimization experience</li><li>Security solution rollout from POC to full deployment; UAT execution; vendor coordination-Must show project implementation ownership</li><li>Managing incidents including zero-day vulnerabilities, patching, misconfigurations-Engineering response, root cause analysis, remediation (not  SOC)</li><li>Networking, Unix/Linux, shell scripting-Required for integration and troubleshooting</li><li>Certifications – SailPoint preferred </li><li>Self-driven, able to work independently, strong stakeholder collaboration</li></ul>",
